<TITLE> 6 dead in Patuakhali road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Patuakhali, Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)At least 6 people were killed including three children and 3 others were injured in a road accident at Rajpara on Saturday. The children Haowa Begum, 2, Abul Kalam, 9, and Raqibul, 10, were playing by the road, police said. Three others who died are a microbus driver, who could not be identified, passengers Shahin, 28, and Zakir, 32. The injured  Babul, 18, Rubel, 14, and Khokon, 22  were taken to Barisal Sher-e-Bangla Medical College. Kalapara Police Station Ishaq Ali told bdnews24.com: "The Barisal-bound microbus was heading from Kuakata." H said the microbus collided with a Nosimon, an improvised human hauler, which was standing beside the road, at 6pm and both fell into a road-side ditch. Raqibul, Kalam, Haowa and the bus driver died on the spot, while Zakir and Shahin died later in the hospital. bdnews24.c
